Config file loader

Source: R/ebirdst-loading.R
load_config.Rd

Internal function used by load_summary(), load_pis(), and load_pds() to get configuration variables from STEM species run information (from *_config.RData).

load_config(path)

Arguments

path

character; full path to the directory containing single species eBird Status and Trends products.

Value

environment object containing all run parameters.

Examples

# \donttest{
# download example data
sp_path <- ebirdst_download("example_data", tifs_only = FALSE)
#> Data already exists, use force = TRUE to re-download.
ebirdst:::load_config(sp_path)
